## Project Summary
This is a browser-based React web app called MeetingMind. It records meeting audio, transcribes speech in real time, generates AI-powered notes and action item summaries, stores them in a cloud database, and provides step-by-step AI guidance on tasks. It must work without any installation on a locked-down office laptop — just Chrome.

## Tech Stack (do not deviate)
- Framework: React 18 with TypeScript
- Build tool: Vite
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v3 + shadcn/ui components
- Routing: react-router-dom v6
- Database + Auth: Supabase (@supabase/supabase-js v2)
- AI Model: Groq API (groq-sdk) — model: llama-3.3-70b-versatile
- Speech: Browser-native Web Speech API (window.webkitSpeechRecognition)
- Icons: lucide-react
- Date formatting: date-fns
- Hosting target: Vercel

## Code Style Rules
- Always use TypeScript. No plain .js files.
- Use functional components and React hooks only. No class components.
- Name components in PascalCase. Name files in kebab-case.
- Keep components small. If a component exceeds 150 lines, split it.
- Use Tailwind utility classes only. Do not write custom CSS files.
- All colours must use the design token variables defined in tailwind.config.ts.
- Never use inline styles.
- Always handle loading and error states explicitly in every component.

## File Structure
src/
  components/       # Reusable UI components
  pages/            # Top-level route components (Dashboard, Session, NoteDetail, Login)
  hooks/            # Custom React hooks (useSpeechRecognition, useNotes, useAuth)
  lib/              # Supabase client, Anthropic client, utility functions
  types/            # TypeScript interfaces and types
  App.tsx           # Router and auth guard
  main.tsx          # Entry point

## Environment Variables
All secrets live in .env (never committed to git).
- VITE_SUPABASE_URL
- VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
- VITE_GROQ_API_KEY
Access via: import.meta.env.VITE_*

## Supabase Rules
- Always use the Supabase client from src/lib/supabase.ts — never initialise it elsewhere.
- Never bypass Row-Level Security. All queries go through the authenticated client.
- Use typed responses: supabase.from('notes').select('*').returns<Note[]>()
- Handle Supabase errors explicitly — never ignore the error object.

## Anthropic API Rules
- Always use model: 'claude-sonnet-4-6'
- Set max_tokens: 1000 for summarisation calls.
- Set max_tokens: 2000 for guidance and chat calls.
- For summarisation, instruct the model to return only valid JSON. Parse safely with try/catch.
- For guidance and chat, use streaming (stream: true) and pipe to the UI word by word.
- Never expose the API key in rendered HTML or console logs.
- Include the full meeting summary as system context when generating task guidance.

## Web Speech API Rules
- Initialise in a custom hook: src/hooks/useSpeechRecognition.ts
- Always set: continuous = true, interimResults = true, lang = 'en-US'
- Distinguish interim results (lighter text) from final results (normal text).
- On recognitionend event, auto-restart if the session is still active (handles browser timeout).
- On error event, set an error state and surface it to the UI. Never swallow errors silently.

## Routing
- /                → redirect to /dashboard if authenticated, else /login
- /login           → Login page
- /dashboard       → Dashboard (protected)
- /session         → Active recording screen (protected)
- /notes/:id       → Note detail view (protected)
- /settings        → Settings (protected)
All protected routes redirect to /login if user is not authenticated.

## UI and Design
- Follow the wireframes in DesignDocument.md exactly.
- Colour palette: primary=#6366F1, background=#F9FAFB, surface=#FFFFFF, recording=#EF4444
- Font: Inter for all UI text; JetBrains Mono for transcript text only.
- Guidance panel slides in from the right on desktop; bottom sheet on mobile.
- All action items are clickable cards with a "Get Help →" button.
- Empty states, error states, and loading states must be implemented for every screen.

## What NOT to do
- Do not use Redux, Zustand, or any external state manager. Use React Context + useState.
- Do not use localStorage or sessionStorage for user data. Use Supabase only.
- Do not use axios. Use the Supabase client and Anthropic SDK which handle HTTP internally.
- Do not use Next.js features (server components, server actions). This is a pure Vite SPA.
- Do not add any package not listed in TechStack.md without asking first.
- Do not generate placeholder or TODO comments — implement the actual logic.
- Do not skip TypeScript types — every function parameter and return value must be typed.
